hh3cIpx.name: hh3cIpx
hh3cIpx.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Tech. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cIpx.description: This MIB defines management information used on products which support ipx protocol. It includes 4 parts: 1.ipx interface configuration group - This group contains configurable management information and statistic information on each interface. 2.rip group - Rip means route information protocol. This group contains configurable management information and route status and route statistic information. 3.sap group - Sap means service access group. This group contains all service information. 4.ipx statistics group - This group includes ipx statistic information on all interfaces.

EnabledStatus.name: EnabledStatus
EnabledStatus.description: A simple status value for the object.

hh3cIpxStatus.name: hh3cIpxStatus
hh3cIpxStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable ipx globally.

hh3cIpxIfConfigTable.name: hh3cIpxIfConfigTable
hh3cIpxIfConfigTable.description: Table of configurable management information on each interface.

hh3cIpxIfConfigEntry.name: hh3cIpxIfConfigEntry
hh3cIpxIfConfigEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing management information about a single interface.

hh3cIpxIfIndex.name: hh3cIpxIfIndex
hh3cIpxIfIndex.description: This variable uniquely identifies the interface to which the configurations are applied.

hh3cIpxIfNetId.name: hh3cIpxIfNetId
hh3cIpxIfNetId.description: The network number of the IPX address of this interface.

hh3cIpxIfNodeId.name: hh3cIpxIfNodeId
hh3cIpxIfNodeId.description: The node number of the IPX address of this interface.

hh3cIpxIfSplitHorizon.name: hh3cIpxIfSplitHorizon
hh3cIpxIfSplitHorizon.description: This node is used to set the split horizon status. Its default value is 'enabled'. In this case, the interface which receives a message can't send this message from the same interface. This function can avoid route loop. But it is unused for point to point link. If it is set to 'disabled', split horizon is disable.

hh3cIPxIfTick.name: hh3cIPxIfTick
hh3cIPxIfTick.description: This object is used to set this interface's delay time. It is counted by ticks which is 1/18 second. By default, the ethernet interface's delay time is 1 tick, asynchronous serial interface's delay time is 30 ticks, WAN interface's delay time is 6 ticks.

hh3cIpxIfUpdateChangeOnly.name: hh3cIpxIfUpdateChangeOnly
hh3cIpxIfUpdateChangeOnly.description: When this variable is set to 'enabled', updating change is on. And sap and rip will send updating packets periodically to avoid broadcast storm. Whereas updating change is off.

hh3cIpxIfRipMtu.name: hh3cIpxIfRipMtu
hh3cIpxIfRipMtu.description: This variable is used to define the max length of RIP updating packets.

hh3cIpxIfEncapsuleType.name: hh3cIpxIfEncapsuleType
hh3cIpxIfEncapsuleType.description: This node is used to define the encapsulating form of IPX packets. 'dot2' indicates the form is 802.2, while 'dot3' means 802.3. And 'snap' indicates the form is ethernet-snap. It takes effect only on ethernet interface, and the default value is 'dot3', while 'unkown' for other types of port.

hh3cIpxIfNetbiosPropagation.name: hh3cIpxIfNetbiosPropagation
hh3cIpxIfNetbiosPropagation.description: This node is used to configure whether the current interface can forward broadcasting packets which IPX type is 20 used for NetBIOS.

hh3cIpxIfSapStatus.name: hh3cIpxIfSapStatus
hh3cIpxIfSapStatus.description: The status of sap on the current interface. It is enabled when ipx is enabled on this interface.

hh3cIpxIfSapMtu.name: hh3cIpxIfSapMtu
hh3cIpxIfSapMtu.description: This variable is used to define the max length of SAP refreshing packets.

hh3cIpxIfGnsReply.name: hh3cIpxIfGnsReply
hh3cIpxIfGnsReply.description: This object is used to enable or disable the current interface to response the IPX GNS request.

hh3cIpxIfRowStatus.name: hh3cIpxIfRowStatus
hh3cIpxIfRowStatus.description: The status of this row. To create a row, user can select 'createAndGo'. If the row is created successfully, this object will became 'active'. To delete one row, user can select 'destory' and the row will be deleted.

hh3cIpxRouteMultiplier.name: hh3cIpxRouteMultiplier
hh3cIpxRouteMultiplier.description: This node is used to calculate Rip aging time of route information. The absolute aging time = (hh3cIpxRouteMultiplier * hh3cIpxRouteUpdateTimer).

hh3cIpxRouteUpdateTimer.name: hh3cIpxRouteUpdateTimer
hh3cIpxRouteUpdateTimer.description: This node is used to set rip updating time which is based on seconds

hh3cIpxRouteImpRouteStatic.name: hh3cIpxRouteImpRouteStatic
hh3cIpxRouteImpRouteStatic.description: This object determines whether static route can be imported.

hh3cIpxRouteLoadBalancePaths.name: hh3cIpxRouteLoadBalancePaths
hh3cIpxRouteLoadBalancePaths.description: This object defines the max equivalent paths to the same destination. If the newly defined value is smaller than the current value, the routes out of the new value will be set inactive.

hh3cIpxRouteMaxResPaths.name: hh3cIpxRouteMaxResPaths
hh3cIpxRouteMaxResPaths.description: This object defines the max dynamic routes to the same destination. If the newly defined value is smaller than the current value, the routes will not be deleted until they age out or are deleted manually.

hh3cIpxRouteTable.name: hh3cIpxRouteTable
hh3cIpxRouteTable.description: This table contains all dynamic and direct ipx route information of this system. The information of this table is read only.

hh3cIpxRouteEntry.name: hh3cIpxRouteEntry
hh3cIpxRouteEntry.description: Each entry includes a dynamic or direct route.

hh3cIpxRouteIndex.name: hh3cIpxRouteIndex
hh3cIpxRouteIndex.description: This object uniquely identifies a route.

hh3cIpxRouteDestNetId.name: hh3cIpxRouteDestNetId
hh3cIpxRouteDestNetId.description: The destination network number of this route information, and its value ranges from 1 to 0xfffffffe.

hh3cIpxRouteNextHop.name: hh3cIpxRouteNextHop
hh3cIpxRouteNextHop.description: The next hop of this route.

hh3cIpxRoutePro.name: hh3cIpxRoutePro
hh3cIpxRoutePro.description: The protocol type of this route information.

hh3cIpxRoutePre.name: hh3cIpxRoutePre
hh3cIpxRoutePre.description: The preference of this route information. The direct route's preference is 0, and it can't be modified. Dynamic route's default preference is 100.

hh3cIpxRouteTicks.name: hh3cIpxRouteTicks
hh3cIpxRouteTicks.description: The time, in ticks, that the packet takes to reach the destination.

hh3cIpxRouteHops.name: hh3cIpxRouteHops
hh3cIpxRouteHops.description: The object indicates the number of hops that the packet must be passed through to reach the destination.

hh3cIpxRouteTime.name: hh3cIpxRouteTime
hh3cIpxRouteTime.description: The aging time of this route information. The aging time of static and interface route information is 0.

hh3cIpxRouteOutInterface.name: hh3cIpxRouteOutInterface
hh3cIpxRouteOutInterface.description: The out interface of this route information.

hh3cIpxStaticRouteTable.name: hh3cIpxStaticRouteTable
hh3cIpxStaticRouteTable.description: This table contains all static ipx route information of this system.

hh3cIpxStaticRouteEntry.name: hh3cIpxStaticRouteEntry
hh3cIpxStaticRouteEntry.description: Each entry includes one static route information.

hh3cIpxStaticRouteDestNetId.name: hh3cIpxStaticRouteDestNetId
hh3cIpxStaticRouteDestNetId.description: The index of Static Route Table. This object and hh3cIpxStaticRouteNextHop uniquely identify a static route. The destination network number of this static route information,and its value ranges from 1 to 0xfffffffe. Note that the broadcast network number is 0xffffffff and is not allowed in IPX. The network number of 0xfffffffe would be considered to be the network number of default route.

hh3cIpxStaticRouteNextHop.name: hh3cIpxStaticRouteNextHop
hh3cIpxStaticRouteNextHop.description: The sub-index of Static Route Table. The next hop of this static route information.

hh3cIpxStaticRoutePre.name: hh3cIpxStaticRoutePre
hh3cIpxStaticRoutePre.description: The preference of this route information. Static route's preference is 60, and it can be configured.

hh3cIpxStaticRouteOutIf.name: hh3cIpxStaticRouteOutIf
hh3cIpxStaticRouteOutIf.description: The out interface of this route. This interface can be serial or pos interface.

hh3cIpxStaticRouteTicks.name: hh3cIpxStaticRouteTicks
hh3cIpxStaticRouteTicks.description: The time, in ticks that the packet takes to reach the destination with the static route.

hh3cIpxStaticRouteHops.name: hh3cIpxStaticRouteHops
hh3cIpxStaticRouteHops.description: This object indicates how many hops are needed to arrive at the destination network.

hh3cIpxStaticRouteStatus.name: hh3cIpxStaticRouteStatus
hh3cIpxStaticRouteStatus.description: The status of this static route.

hh3cIpxStaticRouteRowStatus.name: hh3cIpxStaticRouteRowStatus
hh3cIpxStaticRouteRowStatus.description: The status of this row. To create a row, user can select 'createAndGo'. If the row is created successfully, this object will became 'active'. To delete one row, user can select 'destory' and the row will be deleted.

hh3cIpxRouteStatTable.name: hh3cIpxRouteStatTable
hh3cIpxRouteStatTable.description: A table includes all statistic route information.

hh3cIpxRouteStatEntry.name: hh3cIpxRouteStatEntry
hh3cIpxRouteStatEntry.description: An entry records a statistic information of route.

hh3cIpxRouteStatPro.name: hh3cIpxRouteStatPro
hh3cIpxRouteStatPro.description: The protocol type of the route information. The value of 'total' is the total amount of all kinds of IPX routes.

hh3cIpxRouteStatRoutes.name: hh3cIpxRouteStatRoutes
hh3cIpxRouteStatRoutes.description: The route amount of the corresponding protocol type.

hh3cIpxRouteStatActives.name: hh3cIpxRouteStatActives
hh3cIpxRouteStatActives.description: The active route amount of the corresponding protocol type.

hh3cIpxRouteStatAddeds.name: hh3cIpxRouteStatAddeds
hh3cIpxRouteStatAddeds.description: The added route amount of the corresponding protocol type.

hh3cIpxRouteStatDeleteds.name: hh3cIpxRouteStatDeleteds
hh3cIpxRouteStatDeleteds.description: The deleted but not freed route amount of the corresponding protocol type.

hh3cIpxRouteStatFreeds.name: hh3cIpxRouteStatFreeds
hh3cIpxRouteStatFreeds.description: The freed route amount of the corresponding protocol type.

hh3cIpxSapMultiplier.name: hh3cIpxSapMultiplier
hh3cIpxSapMultiplier.description: This node is used to calculate aging time of service information. The absolute aging time = (hh3cIpxSapMultiplier * hh3cIpxSapUpdateTimer).

hh3cIpxSapUpdateTimer.name: hh3cIpxSapUpdateTimer
hh3cIpxSapUpdateTimer.description: This node is used to set service packet updating time which is based on seconds.

hh3cIpxSapGnsLoadBalance.name: hh3cIpxSapGnsLoadBalance
hh3cIpxSapGnsLoadBalance.description: This object is used to set whether the system will reply to the GNS request with the Round-Robin way. By default, the system will response to the GNS request with the servers known to the device in turn, preventing from the nearest server's over loading. With value of disabled, in this way, the system will response to the request with the nearest server(who has smallest hop in system's service information table).

hh3cIpxSapMaxResServers.name: hh3cIpxSapMaxResServers
hh3cIpxSapMaxResServers.description: This object is used to configure maximum number of servers of a type. If the newly defined value is smaller than the previous value, the information out of the value will not be deleted. If the queue reaches to the maximum number, no new information can be added.

hh3cIpxServiceTable.name: hh3cIpxServiceTable
hh3cIpxServiceTable.description: This table inlcudes all dynamic service information. The dynamic service information can be read only.

hh3cIpxServiceIndex.name: hh3cIpxServiceIndex
hh3cIpxServiceIndex.description: This object uniquely identifies a service information.

hh3cIpxServiceNetId.name: hh3cIpxServiceNetId
hh3cIpxServiceNetId.description: The IPX network number portion of the IPX address of the service.

hh3cIpxServiceNodeId.name: hh3cIpxServiceNodeId
hh3cIpxServiceNodeId.description: The IPX node number portion of the IPX address of the service.

hh3cIpxServiceSocketNo.name: hh3cIpxServiceSocketNo
hh3cIpxServiceSocketNo.description: The socket portion of the IPX address of the service

hh3cIpxServicePreference.name: hh3cIpxServicePreference
hh3cIpxServicePreference.description: The service preference of the service

hh3cIpxServiceHops.name: hh3cIpxServiceHops
hh3cIpxServiceHops.description: The hops from the device to the server.

hh3cIpxServiceRecvIf.name: hh3cIpxServiceRecvIf
hh3cIpxServiceRecvIf.description: Interface from which the service is receieved

hh3cIpxStaticServiceTable.name: hh3cIpxStaticServiceTable
hh3cIpxStaticServiceTable.description: This table inlcudes all static service information. This table supports to creation and deletione of a static service, but not supports to modification

hh3cIpxStaticServiceType.name: hh3cIpxStaticServiceType
hh3cIpxStaticServiceType.description: The index of static service table.

hh3cIpxStaticServiceName.name: hh3cIpxStaticServiceName
hh3cIpxStaticServiceName.description: The sub-index of static service table. The name of the service.

hh3cIpxStaticServiceNetId.name: hh3cIpxStaticServiceNetId
hh3cIpxStaticServiceNetId.description: The sub-index of static service table. The IPX network number portion of the IPX address of the service.

hh3cIpxStaticServiceNodeId.name: hh3cIpxStaticServiceNodeId
hh3cIpxStaticServiceNodeId.description: The IPX node number portion of the IPX address of the service.

hh3cIpxStatciServiceSocketNo.name: hh3cIpxStatciServiceSocketNo
hh3cIpxStatciServiceSocketNo.description: The socket portion of the IPX address of the service.

hh3cIpxStaticServicePreference.name: hh3cIpxStaticServicePreference
hh3cIpxStaticServicePreference.description: The service preference of the server.

hh3cIpxStaticServiceHops.name: hh3cIpxStaticServiceHops
hh3cIpxStaticServiceHops.description: The hops from the device to the server.

hh3cIpxStaticServiceStatus.name: hh3cIpxStaticServiceStatus
hh3cIpxStaticServiceStatus.description: The status of the service that you created. The value of this object is determined by system.

hh3cIpxStaticServiceRowStatus.name: hh3cIpxStaticServiceRowStatus
hh3cIpxStaticServiceRowStatus.description: The status of this row. To create a row, user can select 'createAndGo'. If the row is created successfully, this object will became 'active'. To delete one row, user can select 'destory' and the row will be deleted.

hh3cIpxStatTotalReceives.name: hh3cIpxStatTotalReceives
hh3cIpxStatTotalReceives.description: The total number of packets received.

hh3cIpxStatPitchs.name: hh3cIpxStatPitchs
hh3cIpxStatPitchs.description: The number of received packets filled by device when forwarding or delivering up to upper protocol.

hh3cIpxStatLenErrors.name: hh3cIpxStatLenErrors
hh3cIpxStatLenErrors.description: The number of received packets discarded due to length error.

hh3cIpxStatFormatErrors.name: hh3cIpxStatFormatErrors
hh3cIpxStatFormatErrors.description: The number of received packets discarded due to format error.

hh3cIpxStatBadHops.name: hh3cIpxStatBadHops
hh3cIpxStatBadHops.description: The number of received packets which's value of field Hops is greater than 16.

hh3cIpxStatHopsDiscards.name: hh3cIpxStatHopsDiscards
hh3cIpxStatHopsDiscards.description: The number of received packets of which hops portion is equal to 16.

hh3cIpxStatOtherErrors.name: hh3cIpxStatOtherErrors
hh3cIpxStatOtherErrors.description: The number of received packets discarded due to other error.

hh3cIpxStatLocalDests.name: hh3cIpxStatLocalDests
hh3cIpxStatLocalDests.description: The number of received packets which destination is the local device. Note that this would include the IPX NetBIOS propagation packets and those broadcast packets just to the network on which local device resides.

hh3cIpxStatCantDeals.name: hh3cIpxStatCantDeals
hh3cIpxStatCantDeals.description: The number of received packets with which can't be dealt. One possible reason for discarding such a packet would be receiving a packet of an unknown or unsupported protocol.

hh3cIpxStatForwards.name: hh3cIpxStatForwards
hh3cIpxStatForwards.description: The number of received packets to be forwarded in the case that the entity was not their final destination.

hh3cIpxStatGenerates.name: hh3cIpxStatGenerates
hh3cIpxStatGenerates.description: The number of sent packets that the device generated itself.

hh3cIpxStatNoRoutes.name: hh3cIpxStatNoRoutes
hh3cIpxStatNoRoutes.description: The number of packets discarded due to no route to the destination was found in routing table.

hh3cIpxStatOutDiscards.name: hh3cIpxStatOutDiscards
hh3cIpxStatOutDiscards.description: The number of packets to be discarded when sending out. Note that this counter would not include the packet(s) discarded due to no route.

hh3cIpxStatRipSends.name: hh3cIpxStatRipSends
hh3cIpxStatRipSends.description: The total number of RIP packets sent.

hh3cIpxStatRipReceives.name: hh3cIpxStatRipReceives
hh3cIpxStatRipReceives.description: The total number of RIP packets received.

hh3cIpxStaRipRspSends.name: hh3cIpxStaRipRspSends
hh3cIpxStaRipRspSends.description: The total number of RIP response packets sent.

hh3cIpxStaRipRspReceives.name: hh3cIpxStaRipRspReceives
hh3cIpxStaRipRspReceives.description: The total number of RIP response packets received.

hh3cIpxStatRipReqReceives.name: hh3cIpxStatRipReqReceives
hh3cIpxStatRipReqReceives.description: The total number of RIP request packets received.

hh3cIpxStatRipReqDeals.description: The total number of RIP request packets dealt with.

hh3cIpxStatRipReqSends.description: The total number of RIP request packets sent.

hh3cIpxStatRipPeriUpdates.description: The total number of periodic update RIP packets sent.

hh3cIpxStatSapGenReqReceives.name: hh3cIpxStatSapGenReqReceives
hh3cIpxStatSapGenReqReceives.description: The total number of SAP general request packets received.

hh3cIpxStatSapSpecReqReceives.name: hh3cIpxStatSapSpecReqReceives
hh3cIpxStatSapSpecReqReceives.description: The total number of SAP specific request packets received.

hh3cIpxStatSapGnsReqReceives.description: The total number of SAP GNS request packets received.

hh3cIpxStatSapGenRspSends.name: hh3cIpxStatSapGenRspSends
hh3cIpxStatSapGenRspSends.description: The total number of SAP general response packets sent.

hh3cIpxStatSapSpecRspSends.name: hh3cIpxStatSapSpecRspSends
hh3cIpxStatSapSpecRspSends.description: The total number of SAP specific response packets sent.

hh3cIpxStatSapGnsRspSends.name: hh3cIpxStatSapGnsRspSends
hh3cIpxStatSapGnsRspSends.description: The total number of SAP GNS response packets sent.

hh3cIpxStatSapPeriUpdates.name: hh3cIpxStatSapPeriUpdates
hh3cIpxStatSapPeriUpdates.description: The total number of SAP periodic update packets sent.

hh3cIpxStatSapInPktErrors.name: hh3cIpxStatSapInPktErrors
hh3cIpxStatSapInPktErrors.description: The total number of SAP error packets received.

hh3cIpxIfStatTable.name: hh3cIpxIfStatTable
hh3cIpxIfStatTable.description: The table of the statistic information on each interface.

hh3cIpxIfStatEntry.name: hh3cIpxIfStatEntry
hh3cIpxIfStatEntry.description: The entry of the statistic table.

hh3cIpxIfStatIndex.name: hh3cIpxIfStatIndex
hh3cIpxIfStatIndex.description: The index of the table's entry. According to the interface's index.

hh3cIpxIfStatNetId.name: hh3cIpxIfStatNetId
hh3cIpxIfStatNetId.description: The network number of the IPX address of this interface.

hh3cIpxIfStatNodeId.name: hh3cIpxIfStatNodeId
hh3cIpxIfStatNodeId.description: The node number of the IPX address of this interface.

hh3cIpxIfStatIpxReceives.name: hh3cIpxIfStatIpxReceives
hh3cIpxIfStatIpxReceives.description: The total number of packets received on the interface.

hh3cIpxIfStatIpxSends.description: The total number of packets sent on the interface.

hh3cIpxIfStatIpxRecvBytes.description: The total number of bytes received on the interface.

hh3cIpxIfStatIpxSendBytes.description: The total number of bytes sent on the interface.

hh3cIpxIfStatRipReceives.description: The total number of RIP packets received on the interface.

hh3cIpxIfStatRipDiscards.description: The total number of RIP packets discarded on the interface.

hh3cIpxIfStatRipSpecReqReceives.description: The total number of RIP specific request packets received on the interface.

hh3cIpxIfStatRipSpecRspSends.description: The total number of RIP specific response packets sent on the interface.

hh3cIpxIfStatRipGenReqReceives.name: hh3cIpxIfStatRipGenReqReceives
hh3cIpxIfStatRipGenReqReceives.description: The total number of RIP general request packets received on the interface.

hh3cIpxIfStatRipGenRspSends.description: The total number of RIP general response packets sent on the interface.

hh3cIpxIfStatSapReceives.description: The total number of SAP packets received on the interface.

hh3cIpxIfStatSapGnsReqReceives.description: The total number of SAP GNS response packets received on the interface.
